= Appendix 1: Personal Appraisal #emoji.construction

This project contains several strengths and weaknesses in relation to my performance and methods.

The processes used while implementing the application were particularly strong. I followed common development and operations (DevOps) processes to do with my branching strategy, use of pull requests, issue tracking, automatic AI peer-reviewer in pull requests, and unit testing. This helped prevent slowing down the process of implementation and allowed for a scructured and easy to follow flow during implementation.

The use of existing technologies was good too, as this allowed me to focus on the UI design and backend business logic rather than dwelling on infrastructure and architecture while reducing the technical overhead of more moving pieces to maintain.

That said, during the implementation I frequently overengineered certain aspects, especially the stored unit format, which became a time sink and burden while trying to implement the logic and UI surrounding units.

The literature review is also very vague and general at times, due to a lack of scope at the beginning. The literature review should be more concise and relevant to the final product, which would have led to further pedagogical influence in the design of the system.

During the project I also suffered from a lack of time management and burnout, which meant that although the project was completed on time, several deadlines were missed and became a cascading problem near the end of the project.